+A2pl:+sHnHz	+A2pl:=		+A2pl:+zsHnHz	+A2pl:+nHz
+A3pl:+lAr	+A3pl:=		+A3pl:+zlAr  	+A3pl:+lAr

Imp:		Imp:sA		Opt:	  
+A1sg:-		+A1sg:-		+A1sg:+yHm
+A2sg:0	      	+A2sg:+nA	+A2sg:=	  
+A3sg:+sHn	+A3sg:-		+A3sg:=	  
+A1pl:-	      	+A1pl:-		+A1pl:+lHm
+A2pl:+yHn(Hz)	+A2pl:+nHzA	+A2pl:=	  
+A3pl:+sHnlAr 	+A3pl:-		+A3pl:=   

Other tenses take default suffixes.  Exceptions:
- Narr:mHS+A2sg can also be +Hn (otherwise same as Aor)
- Narr:ymHS+A1pl can also be +Hz (otherwise default)
- Aor/Narr can probably be handled by regex.
- NegAor should use the z suffix, then A1 fixed by regex.

;;; Issue 6: different sets of Tense2 allowed.  By default all Tenses
take Narr, Past, Cond, Cop as second Tense.  Exceptions:

+Aor:+Hr	Cop cannot immediately follow.
+Desr:+sA	Cond/Cop cannot follow.
+Imp:0		Nothing can follow.
+Narr:+mHş	Second Narr rare but observed.
+Opt:+yA	Only Past observed.
+Past:+dH	No Cop/Narr.  Second Past rare.

